    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is designed as a single-page experience with a fixed top navigation bar for easy access to four distinct sections: 'Visión General' (an introduction), 'Guía del Proyecto' (an interactive timeline), 'Herramientas' (resources), and 'Evaluación' (rubrics). This structure was chosen to logically segment the dense information of the original document, allowing users (teacher and students) to quickly jump to the content they need without extensive scrolling. The core interaction is a clickable timeline, which breaks down the project into manageable steps, revealing detailed information on demand. This task-oriented design enhances usability and makes the project guide feel more like an application and less like a static document. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info: Project steps/phases -> Goal: Organize a process -> Viz/Presentation: Interactive vertical timeline built with HTML/CSS. Interaction: Clicking a step reveals its detailed content, hiding others. Justification: A timeline visually represents the project's progression, making it easier to follow than a list. Library/Method: Vanilla JS for click events. | Report Info: Two evaluation rubrics -> Goal: Organize structured data -> Viz/Presentation: HTML tables toggled by buttons. Interaction: Buttons show/hide the relevant rubric. Justification: Toggles prevent clutter, showing only one rubric at a time, which is clearer for the user. Library/Method: Vanilla JS. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
